	<fdd:notes>
		<fdd:general>
			<p> According to <a href="https://documentation.apple.com/en/finalcutpro/professionalformatsandworkflows/index.html#chapter=10%26section=3">Apple</a>, camera formats that would be appropriate to transcode to ProRes 422 include DVCPro HD, HDV, and AVC Intra. Video specialist <a href="http://www.larryjordan.biz/picking-the-right-version-of-prores/">Larry Jordan</a> adds XDCAM EX, XDCAM HD, AVCAM, or P2 to the list. </p>
		</fdd:general>
		<fdd:history>
			<p>Apple ProRes 422 is one of the two original ProRes codecs (along with <fddLink id="fdd000403">Apple Pro Res 422 HQ). </fddLink>. It was originally named Apple ProRes 422 SQ (for standard quality). </p>
		</fdd:history>
